element.name: implemented action
element.documentation: Once an action is begun, it is implemented.

element.name: abandoned action
element.documentation: - прекращенное по какой либо причине действие - оставленное действие

element.name: suspension
element.documentation: - пауза действия на некоторый временной период - A suspension is a temporary hold on an action.

element.name: time period
element.documentation: If an action continues after the end point of the suspension, the suspension still exists but is no longer suspending, and the action continues.

element.name: plan
element.documentation: - plan is a collection of proposed actions linked in some sequence

element.name: plan dependency
element.documentation: связь между - dependency—an indication that one action cannot begin until another completes

element.name: protocol
element.documentation: - protocol is used for standard plans that are repeated many times. - plans is that, while they can copy the dependencies of the protocol, plans can also define new dependencies that might ignore that of the protocol

element.name: software protocol
element.documentation: A software protocol is a protocol that is coded in software, not a protocol in the sense of a communications protocol

element.name: specific resource allocation
element.documentation: - the former links to the asset and the latter to a resource type, which for an asset would be an asset type - уже конкретное выделение данного ресурса данного типа

element.name: temporal resource
element.documentation: - A temporal resource is a specific resource allocation of an asset - It can have not just an amount of time but also a specific time period.

element.name: resource type
element.documentation: - the former links to the asset and the latter to a resource type, which for an asset would be an asset type - уже конкретное выделение данного ресурса данного типа

element.name: asset type
element.documentation: - A temporal resource is a specific resource allocation of an asset - It can have not just an amount of time but also a specific time period.

element.name: start function
element.documentation: A start function contains information on conditions that are likely to trigger the use of a protocol.

element.name: outcome function
element.documentation: - the input is a combination of protocols and observation concepts - The result is two sets of observation concepts.

element.name: observation concept
element.documentation: Some observation concepts represent the target use of the protocol, that is, the effects that represent the purpose of the protocol. The other obser- vation concepts are the side effects.

element.name: observation
element.documentation: - observations are a subtype of actions. - They can be scheduled, timed, have performers, and be parts of plans. Their additional behavior is that they identify an observation concept or measure a phenomenon type

relationship.name: N|0 - N|0 replacements
relationship.documentation: Plans are always subject to change and can be replaced by other plans,

relationship.name: N|0 - 1 steps
relationship.documentation: - directed acyclic graph (DAG) - because one protocol can appear as more than one step in another parent protocol
Resource allocations can also be used by protocols to describe the resources needed for a protocol to be carried out. In this case we use general resource allocations.

relationship.name: N|0 - N|0 trigger for
relationship.documentation: outcomes are observations linked to the actions within the plan
